output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who are current living in each region 3 years after graduation, male and female Level 7 (research) graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry 3 years after graduation, the region that saw the highest number of students
                    studying there was London . The region with the lowest number of students studying
                    there was South West . The region with the highest number of graduates living
                    there 3 years after graduation was East Midlands  and the region with the
                    least graduates living there was West Midlands .
output.maptext2:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the highest proportionate increase in graduates who studied there compared to living
                    there 3 years after graduation is North East , where the number of
                    graduates increased by NA %. The region with the largest
                    decrease is London where the number of graduates decreased by -68.7 %.
